05:23.113 --> 05:26.537
years? The market was, the industry was very 
depressed until 1973. Why was it depressed until

05:33.127 --> 05:34.789
73? There was an excess supply of oil. In fact, in 
the early 60s, there was so much excess oil that the

05:39.615 --> 05:50.709
Texas Railroad Commission prorated or limited 
the amount of production that could be produced.

05:51.890 --> 05:55.134
And they called it so many producing days. We got 
down as low as you could only produce eight days a

05:55.215 --> 05:59.640
month. and your wells had to be shut in the other 22 
days a month. Actually, they would let you prorate

06:04.978 --> 06:14.533
over the entire period, but you could only produce 
it like 25, 26% of what the well was capable of

06:04.978 --> 06:14.533
producing. Was there no proration before the 
1960s? No, there was proration, but we just had

06:17.017 --> 06:23.187
ended up with an excess, more and more excess oil. 
And so in order to keep the price from just

06:26.468 --> 06:32.674
absolutely going to 10 cents a barrel or 
something, then they cut back production and that

06:26.468 --> 06:32.674
stabilized the price. In fact, the Texas Railroad 
Commission, although they denied it, was the

06:33.374 --> 06:38.439
first OPEC. They were the first oil cartel all by 
themselves. So where was Texas oil coming from? If

06:44.224 --> 06:48.088
Texas was choked back, where was the oil coming 
from? Well, even at producing at that level of

06:48.108 --> 06:55.294
production, Texas is 35% of the total oil in the 
United States. And so choking Texas back to 25% of

06:55.882 --> 07:05.096
their capability, then we were producing only 
enough oil to meet the demand. But 75% of Texas

07:06.017 --> 07:11.505
production was shut in then. And so the industry 
was very depressed because we had an excess of oil

07:11.545 --> 07:18.295
and very low prices. a very low income level, and it 
stayed that way until 1973 when the Arabs put an

07:18.967 --> 07:29.141
embargo of oil on the United States. What year was 
OPEC formed? Well, it probably was formed in, I

07:31.404 --> 07:40.696
don't know, maybe prior to 1970, but they really 
did not have any power. I mean, we were importing

07:40.816 --> 07:46.864
probably 40% of our oil, but they actually cut off 
All of our supply, OPEC cut off all of our supply in

07:47.063 --> 07:51.350
1973. So before that, so OPEC first exercised its 
power in 1973. Before that, it didn't exercise its

07:57.141 --> 08:00.186
power either positively or negatively. That's 
correct. Okay. Their first impact was in 1973, and

08:02.209 --> 08:11.265
when they cut off the oil supply, we immediately 
had a monstrous gasoline shortage. there would be

08:12.022 --> 08:20.815
sometimes it would take you two or three hours of 
waiting in line just to get gasoline and that was

08:12.022 --> 08:20.815
common all over the United States in 1973. Price of 
oil immediately went to six dollars a barrel, went

08:22.397 --> 08:27.805
from less than three to over six dollars a barrel. 
At that point also Texas had run out of spare

08:29.026 --> 08:39.261
capacity and essentially was up to a hundred 
percent of capacity up from, remember they'd had

08:39.646 --> 08:46.372
75% of their production shut in in the late 50s, 
early 60s. So Texas was at 100% of capacity. The oil

08:50.676 --> 08:53.579
price had now doubled to $6 a barrel. So we began in 
73 to be really good economic years for the

08:54.420 --> 09:08.573
petroleum industry through 1985.

